Ingredients
- 4 chopped strips of bacon
- 1.5 lbs ground beef
- 1 diced yellow onion
- 1 diced bell pepper
- 3 minced garlic cloves
- 2 tbsp chili powder
- 1 tbsp ground cumin
- 2 tsp paprika
- 1 tsp dried oregano
- 1 tsp salt
- 2 tbsp tomato paste
- 28 oz diced fire-roasted tomatoes
- 15 oz black beans (drained and rinsed)
- 15 oz red kidney beans (drained and rinsed)
- 2 cups beef broth
- 1 bay leaf

Directions
1. Heat large pot on medium heat, add bacon and cook until crispy. 
2. Add onion and bell pepper, cook until softened (5 mins).
3. Add garlic and stir (30 seconds).
4. Add ground beef, break into pieces. Cook through.
5. Reduce heat to med-low. Stir in tomato paste and dry spices. Cook until fragrant (2 mins).
6. Add canned tomatoes, beans, broth, and bay leaf. Mix.
7. Increase heat to high. Bring to boil.
8. Reduce heat to medium-low again. Let simmer for 30 minutes uncovered. Stir occasionally.

(Remember to remove bay leaf before serving)
